  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In this work, we benchmarking the effect of all the three steps,combing the effect of first two steps: constructing the vocabulary and adding candidate tokens from the target domain to finalize the vocabulary for integration into the LLM as one, and then checking effect of last step: on how to train the embeddings.",
    "We consider two types of datasets while constructing the vocabularies to be added to the PLM vocabulary: (i) PubMed Abstract Collection (PAC), a collection of around 300K PubMed abstracts used for intermediate fine-tuning by MEDVOC (Balde et al., 2024b), and (ii) Target Task (TGT Task), the target downstream task dataset for which the vocabulary is to be constructed.",
    "We now describe the different vocabulary adaptation methods used for our benchmarking study.",
    "MEDVOC (Balde et al., 2024b) is a SoTA vocabulary adaptation strategy for adapting PLMs like BART and PEGASUS, on medical summarization tasks.",
    "First, candidate vocabularies are constructed on the medical OOV words from a domain-specific corpus (PAC) -V PAC, and a downstream task dataset -V TGT."
